##ECMO playing God in the new Crown Disease? Expert: Does Not have the large-scale promotion condition, not all people apply

Micro Signal deeptechchina

Function description DeepTech is a full-chain content, service, data and investment and financing platform focusing on the emerging technology industrialization, and is committed to building a global network of scientific and technological innovation cooperation.

After Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital successfully treated a newly-crowned patient with ECMO (Extracorporeal membrane oxygenation) , cases of ECMO in critically ill patients emerged in Shanghai and Gansu.

Ko Wen-je, now Taipei's mayor and a professor at the Qiantai University Hospital, was the first person to introduce the technology to the Greater China, saying, "ECMO does too much, and doctors become gods. ".

"when all the means are exhausted and the patient can not be kept alive, ECMO can prolong the life-death threshold, " said Hou Xiaotong, director of the Critical Care Center for cardiac surgery at the Capital University of Medical Sciences, "ECMO is not a panacea. It is not a cure-all. "

What role is this so-called "snatch time from the jaws of death" playing in the new crown epidemic?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(photo: Kaiser Health News)

Not all critically ill patients are eligible

ECMO is an extracorporeal breathing device used to assist patients with severe heart and lung failure. It is called ECMO, or artificial lung. It works by pumping blood from a vein, passing it through a membrane that oxygenates hemoglobin and removes carbon dioxide, and then pumping the gas-exchanged blood back into the patient.

ECMO, as a technique for treating severe cases, is not in itself aimed at the pneumonia. But the new coronavirus's main target is the lung, the patient will usually present the respiratory insufficiency, the hypoxemia and so on, this conforms to ECMO's indication, therefore in the life critical situation, some patients can use the device for adjuvant treatment.

Video | ECMO Technology Principles Animation (Source: Youtube)

Xia Jian, deputy director of the emergency center of Zhongnan Hospital and Director of the emergency and Critical Care Mobile ECMO center, told China News Service: "The lung function of the patients who have received ECMO technical diagnosis and treatment has been damaged to a certain extent. It is impossible for them to recover to a completely normal level, but the remaining, functioning lungs can support normal function in normal times. "

But it's not suitable for all critically ill patients. One assumption is that only patients with ECMO removed can have their lung function restored and other organs function better. The majority of the people suffering from this disease are the elderly, and their basic pathological changes are more serious. In this case, the risk of death would be higher using ECMO.

Ji Bingyang, director of the extracorporeal circulation center at Fuwai Hospital of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, said that related accidents and complications may also occur during use, including bleeding, thrombosis, infection, limb ischemia and multiple organ failure, in severe cases, life-threatening. So in patient selection, people with no underlying disease and relatively strong immunity will be given preference for ECMO.

The biggest problem is that there are very few successful cases of ECMO in patients with NCP. On Monday, Zhang Dingyu, director of Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, accepted an invitation from a group of Chinese doctors in North America to give a report on the progress of treatment for the new coronavirus. ECMO extubation is rarely successful in critically ill patients once the lungs are in the mold, and the mortality rate is high, it said. Zhang dingyu said that the patients who got into Ecmo only heard that Professor Peng Zhiyong of the central South Hospital had saved one patient, while the others had not seen a live patient.

Facing the new crown, does not have the large-scale promotion condition

There are only 4 units in the central South Hospital mentioned above, 2 of which are transferred from other hospitals. Among the top three hospitals in Wuhan, there is only one in the People's Hospital of Wuhan and two in the Central Hospital of Wuhan. Therefore, with limited resources, ECMO can only be used in "critically ill" patients with NCP.

Some data show that China's current stock of ECMO is about 400(excluding Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan) . Another expert said that 2018 statistics showed that China has 260 hospitals can do ECMO, most of which are top three hospitals. By comparison, the 2019 figure for the number of U.S. hospitals that offer ECMO is 264, not far off.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital Uses Ecmo to cure patients with new pneumonia (Source: Zhongnan Hospital Doctors) 

Many hospitals in China want to do ECMO, but the hospital and the medical staff's technology can not meet the operational requirements.

It is understood that starting an ECMO generally requires more than five professional health care teams, and different types require different professional health care personnel, cardiac surgery, cardiopulmonary bypass, ICU doctors, Icu nurses, respiratory doctors, emergency physician, ultrasound doctors, etc. . The management of complications, anticoagulation, and how to remove the machine all need technical treatment and professional assessment.

Because many hospitals have fewer than five Ecmos a year, specialist doctors are in short supply, and there may not be more than 2,000 doctors in 260 hospitals nationwide.

In addition, ECMO also needs to cooperate with a variety of equipment, such as breathing machine, blood filter, intra-aortic balloon counterpulsation and so on.

As a high-end technology device, ECMO seems expensive. But from a machine's point of view, an ECMO costs around 1 million yuan, which is not very expensive in medical devices, and an ultrasound scalpel costs more than 300,000 yuan.

The reason why many people feel that "ECMO rings once, the Gold is tens of thousands of taels" is mainly because the prices of consumables such as the head of the centrifugal pump, the pipes and the lung membranes needed to start the machine are relatively expensive. The cost of a set varies from 50,000 to 100,000 yuan, a patient's consumables can be used continuously, but the daily cost of ICU, medication and monitoring equipment is about 10,000 to 20,000 yuan.

Above all, in this epidemic, a short period of time to promote the use of large-scale ECMO almost impossible to achieve. ECMO gives a patient's heart and lungs a break, and treatment of the underlying condition remains critical.
